quest_title: A train "A" is traveling at a speed of 108km/hr. The train approaching another train "B" standing on the platform. The engine of the train 'B' blow its horn. The frequency of horn as observed by driver in train A is 504Hz. the frequency of horn of train "B" (speed of sound = 330m/sec)
explanation_txt:
\(\mathrm{f}=504 \mathrm{Hz}\)
\(\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{s}}=108 \mathrm{km} / \mathrm{hr}=108 \times \cfrac{5}{18} \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{sec}=30 \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{sec} \mathrm{c}\)
\(\mathrm{V}=330 \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{sec}\)
\(\mathrm{f}^{1}=\left(\cfrac{\mathrm{v}}{v-v_{s}}\right) \times \mathrm{f}\)
\(\mathrm{f}=504 \times\left(\cfrac{330-30}{330}\right)=458.18 \mathrm{Hz}=458 \mathrm{Hz}\)

quest_title: Two capacitors of capacitance 1 \(\mu\)F and 2 \(\mu\)F are connected in series, the breakdown voltages of the capacitors are 10 kV and 6 kV respectively. What is the maximum voltage that could be applied across their combination?
explanation_txt:
\(\left(q_{1}\right)_{\max }=C_{1} \times V_{b r}\)

\(\left(q_{1}\right)_{\max }=1 \times 10^{-6} \times 10 \times 10^{3} \mathrm{C}\)

\(\left(q_{1}\right)_{\max }=10 \times 10^{-3} \mathrm{C}\)

\(\left(q_{2}\right)_{\max }=C_{2} \times V_{b r}\)

\(\left(q_{2}\right)_{\max }=2 \times 10^{-6} \times 6 \times 10^{3} \mathrm{C}\)

\(\left(q_{2}\right)_{\max }=12 \times 10^{-3} \mathrm{C}\)

Here smaller charge is \(10 \times 10^{-3} \mathrm{C}\) . This charge is taken in series circuit.

\(\begin{aligned} \text { Now, } V &=V_{1}+V_{2} \\ V &=\cfrac{q}{C_{1}}+\cfrac{q}{C_{2}} \\ V &=\cfrac{10 \times 10^{-3}}{1 \times 10^{-6}}+\cfrac{10 \times 10^{-3}}{2 \times 10^{-3}} \\ V&=10 \times 10^3 + 5 \times 10^3 \\ V & = 15 \times 10^3 \, V \end{aligned}\)
